                    <p class="text-orange-900 text-sm">Transport workers employed <strong>outside Metro Vancouver</strong> (e.g., Fraser Valley, Okanagan, Northern BC) qualify for an additional <strong>5–25 regional points</strong> in the SIRS scoring grid. For truck drivers and bus operators whose wages are in the mid-range, regional points can be the deciding factor in receiving a registration invitation.</p>
                </div>
